## Roles & Permissions

### Three roles (slug-based)
`owner` → `manager` → `staff`

Owner bypasses ALL permission checks automatically.

### Permission resolution (`HasPermissions` trait on `User`)
```
1. role.slug === 'owner' → always true
2. user_permission pivot (explicit grant/deny override)
3. role's default permissions (role_permission pivot)
4. false
```

### Middleware
- `can:device.manage` — Laravel Gate alias → calls `hasPermission()`
- `permission:slug` — `RequirePermission` middleware
- `role:owner` / `role:manager,owner` — `RequireRole` middleware (older pattern, still used in some routes)

### Admin UI
`Settings → Roles & Permissions` — per-user permission overrides via `PUT /api/users/{id}/permissions`.
Frontend uses `usePermissions()` hook → calls `GET /api/auth/me` which includes `permissions[]`.

### Planned (not yet implemented)
- Migrate remaining `role:` middleware in `api.php` / `api_finance.php` to `permission:` slugs
- Add customer-token blocking inside `RequirePermission::handle()` (currently only in `RequireRole`)
- Replace `RoleGuard` with `PermissionGuard` in `App.tsx`
- Filter sidebar nav by `can(slug)` in `Layout.tsx`

