## API Route Structure

```php
// api.php
Route::get('/health') // public
Route::get('/opening-hours') // public
Route::prefix('auth/staff') // login
Route::prefix('auth/customer') // OTP

// Staff-authenticated block
Route::middleware(['auth:sanctum', 'staff.token'])->group(function () {
    // All admin routes (Orders, KDS, Inventory, Shifts, Reports, etc.)
    require __DIR__ . '/api_finance.php'; // invoices, expenses, P&L, forecasts, suppliers
});

// Customer-authenticated block
Route::middleware(['auth:sanctum', 'customer.token'])->prefix('customer')-> // orders, profile

// Public menu
Route::get('/categories') Route::get('/items')

// Site settings CMS
Route::get('/site-settings/public') // public
Route::get('/site-settings') + Route::put() + Route::post('/upload') // owner only
```

